info.description:
Description-dimensions:
EL 143.0 mm ; EWe 84.2 ; EWbt 28.7 ; max. T. 9.0 ; wt 335.8 g
Typology:
Faces appear to have been virt. flat in cross section - sides slightly bowed poss with tendency to double facetting - but no crisp bevel extant ; intact body angles fairly crisp with minimal lipping in evidence; certainly no central bevel; despite loss of sur. but had evid. been pretty thin.
Manufacture:
Evid. for moderately set e. bev. - crest of bevel just perceptible in spots; some monor asymmetry in provilfe - but slightly flattter face is more curved close to butt than is reverse.  
Condition:
No indication of dam. prior to corrosion etc. ; score/rub marks down either butt side & file ripples across either butt side, all assoc. with gold flecking - modern interference by finder and his colleagues ; none of c.e. intact
Attached material:
v. little trace of yellow soil, in one case forming accretion like spot with admixture of white grains (calcium?)

info.description:
Description - dimensions: 
L. 138.5 ; We 77.0 ; Wbt 24.8 ; max B. fg. 12.4 ; Tst 11.2 ; T.e. bev. 10.0 ; Tbt 1.5
Typology:
quite regular low flanges - sl. indentations on inner faces ; sl. curved st. bev. ; e. bev. with broad furrows above ; rounded bev. at base of panel of decn. ; sl. thick bt. - not flat tipped, two bevelled surfaces ; loz. facets on sides, and tendency towards narrow longitudinal facets bordering flange crests.
Manufacture:
panel of dect. sl. irreg. vert. columns of chevrons; on one face a few pmks extend onto furrow - these seem more blurred, poss. pre-furrow manu.; hmks on sides within facets; v. fine "brush" scoremarks across edge - poss orig. gmks.
Condition:
part of edge mainly intact & sharp; much sl. dam. by p. clipping & by dent - prob. ancient origin - poss. mod. interference as well; blade tips intact original; series of hmks define lowest lozenge on either side- ancient.
